    "headline": "Honeywell Technologies raises profit guidance after one-for-two reverse stock split",
    "summary": "Automation firm Honeywell Technologies on Wednesday raised ‌its second-half and full-year ‌profit targets for 2026 after completing a ​one-for-two reverse stock split. The company, formerly Honeywell, proceeded with the split after spinning off and ‌listing its aerospace ⁠arm, Honeywell Aerospace, last month. Honeywell Technologies ⁠expects second-half adjusted earnings per share in the range of $4.40 ​to $4.70, compared ​with $2.20 to $2.35 ​earlier.",
